title: Mother's Banana Bread
desc: This is an old recipe that belonged to my mother.  I've been making this bread since I was a teenager.  At a candy striper bake sale a doctor bought this bread and said that this was the best banana bread that he had tasted.

title: Pumpernickel Bread I
desc: This recipe makes a loaf that is not the very heavy textured bread made from the book that comes with the bread machine.

title: Sun Dried Tomato Focaccia
desc: This isn't just a bread, it's a meal - chewy foccacia with a cheese topping.

title: Buttermilk Bread I
desc: This is a great bread recipe for your bread machine.  It's easy and very good.

title: Michell Jenny's Challah
desc: This our family favorite. The recipe was a gift from my best friend.

title: Potato Bread I
desc: Bread machine recipe.  White bread with some wholesome ingredients.

title: Cinnamon Cranraisin Bread
desc: Excellent breakfast bread to be made in bread machine with cinnamon and dried cranberries.

title: Delicious Pumpkin Bread
desc: Got this recipe from my mom. It is a pretty good recipe, and can be made with canned or fresh pumpkin. One half cup raisins may be substituted for the nuts.

title: Mom's Zucchini Bread
desc: Really, really good and moist- my kids eat it as quickly as I can make it.  Bread will freeze well, and keep in refrigerator for weeks.

title: Molasses-Oat Bran Bread
desc: This recipe for a healthy, semi-sweet, dark, and hearty loaf of bread features molasses and oat bran.

title: Fabulous Homemade Bread
desc: Best Homemade Bread - 6 loaves in less than 3 hours!  This is a variation of my mother Elaine's recipe.  She is 75, and still makes hers by hand.  I cheat and use a Bosch mixer, that's my time saver.

title: Persimmon Bread I
desc: Nice, moist bread.

title: Cinnamon Carrot Bread
desc: I don't remember where I got this recipe, but I have had it for about 20 years.  It is a real good bread.

title: Nick's Favorite Cherry Pecan Bread
desc: One of my son's favorite breads.  You can ice top with a powdered sugar glaze if you wish.

title: Alienated Blueberry Muffins
desc: I got this recipe from my grandmother in New Jersey. They fit the title, because they are out of this world!

title: Swedish Rye Bread I
desc: This is excellent bread, so good it melts in your mouth!

title: Bran Muffins I
desc: This muffin batter can be mixed up ahead of time, and kept in the refrigerator for up to a week for fresh muffins any time.

title: Zucchini Walnut Bread
desc: A delicious, moist, bread which may be glazed with confectioners' sugar, even better after frozen.

title: Apricot Nut Bread
desc: If you like apricots--you'll love this one.

title: Babka I
desc: Traditional Polish Easter bread. Serve as a coffee cake for breakfast or with tea. The recipe makes 3 large loaves.

title: Brazilian Banana Bread
desc: In Brazil we call this Banana Cake, but when I baked this for the first time here everyone started calling it Banana Bread. You can add nuts in the dough or on the top if you wish.

title: Easy Banana Bread
desc: My family lives for banana bread, and they all say this recipe is heaven!

title: Banana Oat Muffins
desc: A healthy and delicious morning treat!

title: Canadian Doughnuts
desc: If you ever visited Ottawa, Ontario, Canada, in the winter months on the Rideau Canal, which is the longest skating rink in the world, they serve 'Beaver Tails,' a sweet pastry that is essentially a flat doughnut with sugar on top. I could not get the authentic recipe since it is their trade secret, but I created a replica of what they serve.

title: Beer Biscuits
desc: The beer adds flavor and leavening to these biscuits.

title: Beer Bread I
desc: Beer Bread is a quick bread to make to accompany any beef dish.  The type of beer you use will change the taste.

title: Cardamom Bread
desc: This makes a lovely tea bread, and is kneaded in the bread machine.  You can also hand knead the dough.

title: Three C Bread
desc: Very healthy bread--kids even like it.

title: Grandma Cornish's Whole Wheat Potato Bread
desc: This is the recipe that my husband's grandmother made for her family, my mother-in-law made for hers, and I have inherited the fun of making this bread for mine.  We particularly like this fresh out of the oven, and then eat it daily for breakfast.  My father-in-law at 86 years old bragged about never having eaten a slice of 'store bought bread.'

title: Chocolate Bread
desc: This chocolate bread doesn't taste sweet.  It tastes savory, and is good with cream cheese!
